race.description: Beverley & Trevor Curtis - Life Members Handicap
race.comment: DAISYDOO (1) has been excellent in both runs this prep, narrowly missing fresh before rattling home again into the frame here last time. On the quick back-up and rising in trip, she maps to blend in beautifully from the middle draw and will be very hard to hold out late. LAYIN' UP (9) hit the line full of running at headquarters and looks dangerous if Milnes can have her a shade closer from the inside draw. PALM OF JUMEIRAH (2) found Flemington a touch sharp last start but this is a far easier assignment, and her best figures make her one of the key hopes. MISLUDI (12) is always strong late and will be hoping for genuine speed to bring her into it, though the tempo looks only moderate, so caution advised. CHILLCUZ (11) continues to race well and gets in light with the claim, keeping her in the mix.
